        <num>CC 1862</num>
        <heading>1862.  Place of performance</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1862.  Place of performance
Performance shall be rendered in the place either stipulated in the agreement or intended by the parties according to usage, the nature of the performance, or other circumstances.
In the absence of agreement or other indication of the parties' intent, performance of an obligation to give an individually determined thing shall be rendered at the place the thing was when the obligation arose.  If the obligation is of any other kind, the performance shall be rendered at the domicile of the obligor.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109104</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
